3 Univariate Analysis

3.1 AGE_group

AGE_group and Post_LOS (baseline group is age over 50)

uni1<-svyglm(Post_LOS~as.factor(AGE_group), data=ps_model1_overlap, design = Post_LOS_MA)
tidy(uni1)

3.2 Sex

Sex and Post_LOS (baseline is male)

uni2<-svyglm(Post_LOS~Sex, data=ps_model1_overlap, design = Post_LOS_MA)
tidy(uni2)

3.3 BMI_group2

BMI_group2 and Post_LOS (baseline group is Overweight)

uni3<-svyglm(Post_LOS~BMI_group2, data=ps_model1_overlap, design=Post_LOS_MA)
tidy(uni3)

3.4 ASA2

ASA2 and Post_LOS (baseline group is normal weight)

uni4<-svyglm(Post_LOS~ASA2, data=ps_model1_overlap, design=Post_LOS_MA)
tidy(uni4)

3.5 PRI

PRI and Post_LOS (baseline group is hernia size less than 1.5)

uni5<-svyglm(Post_LOS~PRI, data=ps_model1_overlap, design=Post_LOS_MA)
tidy(uni5)

3.6 TECHNIQUE

uni6<-svyglm(Post_LOS~TECHNIQUE, data=ps_model1_overlap, design=Post_LOS_MA)
